ALONG WITH THE CITY'S GRADUAL URBANIZATION, THE SETTLEMENT'S POPULATION ALSO RAPIDLY INCREASED. BEACH RESORTS, LODGES, HOUSES AND RESTAURANTS MUSHROOMED IN THE AREA ATTRACTING MIGRANTS WHO EVENTUALLY SETTLED IN DUE TO EASY ACCESS TO JOBS AND MARINE RESOURCES. THE EARLY SETTLERS CLAIMED THAT LAND OWNERS OF THE LAND AREA ARE UNKNOWN UNTIL A CASE WAS FILED FOR EVICTION IN YEAR 2000 EXCEPT THAT ADMINISTRATORS OF THE PROPERTY WERE KNOWN AS LOLA DORIS AND EVENTUALLY TIMOTEO CONSING. AT PRESENT, THE LAND IS BEING CLAIMED BY THE HEIRS OF YUSAY. A PENDING CASE FOR APPEAL WAS LIKEWISE FILED BY THE BARANGAY THROUGH ITS CHAIRWOMAN MINERVA
